00:05:46.750 --> 00:05:50.110
In mass production, quality
was treated as a second step.

00:05:50.110 --> 00:05:52.120
We inspect, and we correct.

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:54.040
In lean thinking, it's built--

00:05:54.040 --> 00:05:59.290
the quality is built in at
every step of the whole activity

00:05:59.290 --> 00:06:01.580
from engineering right
through production.

00:06:01.580 --> 00:06:04.960
And one of the things that was
so hard for Westerners to grasp

00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:09.730
was most Westerners thought
I'll give you a quality output,

00:06:09.730 --> 00:06:11.650
but it's going to
cost you more money.

00:06:11.650 --> 00:06:14.910
And what the Japanese found was
I'll give you a quality output,

00:06:14.910 --> 00:06:16.750
and it costs less money.

00:06:16.750 --> 00:06:19.493
Quality-- and this is really
important in health care.

00:06:19.493 --> 00:06:21.160
This is really important
in health care.

00:06:21.160 --> 00:06:24.840
Focusing on quality
will drive down cost.

00:06:24.840 --> 00:06:26.400
It always has.

00:06:26.400 --> 00:06:28.290
Business strategy here
