00:36:57.980 --> 00:36:59.250
to the enterprise.

00:36:59.250 --> 00:37:02.360
So there's this kind
of value relationship

00:37:02.360 --> 00:37:05.720
going on here in an enterprise.

00:37:05.720 --> 00:37:07.220
And now what's a
lean enterprise?

00:37:07.220 --> 00:37:09.320
When we started
this work, we said

00:37:09.320 --> 00:37:12.110
this is a lean enterprise
course or a lean enterprise

00:37:12.110 --> 00:37:13.130
initiative.

00:37:13.130 --> 00:37:15.300
People said, well, what
is a lean enterprise?

00:37:15.300 --> 00:37:16.817
It turns out that's
a good question.

00:37:16.817 --> 00:37:17.900
And here's our definition.

00:37:17.900 --> 00:37:19.410
It's an enterprise of--

00:37:19.410 --> 00:37:22.370
it's an integrated entity
that officially creates

00:37:22.370 --> 00:37:24.920
value for its
multiple stakeholders

00:37:24.920 --> 00:37:27.020
by employing the principles
and practices we're

00:37:27.020 --> 00:37:28.270
going to cover in this course.

00:37:30.920 --> 00:37:34.390
Now, these principles apply
across the entire enterprise.

00:37:34.390 --> 00:37:37.360
So, in an engineering
enterprise,

00:37:37.360 --> 00:37:39.610
you have generally what's
called the product lifecycle

00:37:39.610 --> 00:37:44.820
from the initial concept
of a product like this

00:37:44.820 --> 00:37:48.187
through the design,
definition, design, getting

00:37:48.187 --> 00:37:49.770
the supply chain
lined up, production,

00:37:49.770 --> 00:37:51.100
and distribution of support.

00:37:51.100 --> 00:37:54.060
That's what generates
money for the enterprise,

00:37:54.060 --> 00:37:55.740
selling this product.

00:37:55.740 --> 00:38:01.870
But it also has finance,
information technology,

00:38:01.870 --> 00:38:04.850
human resources, various support
functions which are needed,

00:38:04.850 --> 00:38:06.820
and the leadership processes.

00:38:06.820 --> 00:38:08.680
And the point is lean
applies to all these.

00:38:08.680 --> 00:38:10.685
It doesn't apply just
to manufacturing.

00:38:10.685 --> 00:38:12.310
It applies across
the whole enterprise.

00:38:12.310 --> 00:38:15.313
And we'll show you an
example of that in a minute.

00:38:15.313 --> 00:38:16.980
In health care, it's
very much the same.

00:38:16.980 --> 00:38:18.688
Instead of having the
product life cycle,

00:38:18.688 --> 00:38:21.310
you have the patient life cycle.

00:38:21.310 --> 00:38:23.950
So lean doesn't apply
just to treatment.

00:38:23.950 --> 00:38:28.090
It applies from
preventive monitoring

00:38:28.090 --> 00:38:30.070
through long-term
care management.

00:38:30.070 --> 00:38:31.695
We should really be
thinking-- in fact,

00:38:31.695 --> 00:38:34.195
there are people who feel that
the health care system should

00:38:34.195 --> 00:38:35.310
be reorganized along--

00:38:38.010 --> 00:38:40.460
let's call them disease
pathways or something

00:38:40.460 --> 00:38:45.168
like that, instead of segmented
into imaging and so on.

00:38:45.168 --> 00:38:47.210
And again you have the
same supporting functions.

00:38:47.210 --> 00:38:49.970
And I'm really glad that a
couple of our students here

00:38:49.970 --> 00:38:53.150
in health care are
administrative fellows,

00:38:53.150 --> 00:38:55.040
looking into health
care administration.

00:38:55.040 --> 00:38:57.860
That's really important.

00:38:57.860 --> 00:39:00.410
OK, so does it work?

00:39:00.410 --> 00:39:04.320
Well, I told you how
LAI got started in 1992.

00:39:04.320 --> 00:39:06.980
And it took us 10 years
to respond to the general

00:39:06.980 --> 00:39:08.540
with a book we wrote.

00:39:08.540 --> 00:39:11.180
And we said-- after 10 years,
we said to the general--

00:39:11.180 --> 00:39:14.390
by then, we'd been through
three or four generals.

00:39:14.390 --> 00:39:19.120
And we said, yes, lean does
apply to aerospace if we take

00:39:19.120 --> 00:39:20.740
it at the enterprise level.

00:39:20.740 --> 00:39:22.930
If it's applied to all the
functions of aerospace,

00:39:22.930 --> 00:39:26.820
not just to manufacturing.

00:39:26.820 --> 00:39:31.330
OK, here's a really good
example of the F-18 aircraft.

00:39:31.330 --> 00:39:36.180
This is a fighter
aircraft for the Navy.

00:39:36.180 --> 00:39:38.190
They were going through
an upgrade to the model

00:39:38.190 --> 00:39:40.990
E/F. It was an upgrade,
but it was actually

00:39:40.990 --> 00:39:42.090
a completely new aircraft.

00:39:42.090 --> 00:39:44.310
It was 25% bigger, but
it was sold to Congress

00:39:44.310 --> 00:39:48.850
as an upgrade, $5 billion
budget, 8 and 1/2 years

00:39:48.850 --> 00:39:52.390
to do the engineering
and design.

00:39:52.390 --> 00:39:57.080
The program performed
on schedule within cost,

00:39:57.080 --> 00:39:59.990
met all its technical
requirements,

00:39:59.990 --> 00:40:02.510
very unusual compared to those
burning platform programs

00:40:02.510 --> 00:40:03.320
I showed you.

00:40:03.320 --> 00:40:06.230
And, when we went in and
studied it and looked

00:40:06.230 --> 00:40:08.930
at what they'd done with
what the lean principles are,

00:40:08.930 --> 00:40:10.643
they were a lean enterprise.

00:40:10.643 --> 00:40:12.560
They didn't call themselves
a lean enterprise,

00:40:12.560 --> 00:40:13.700
but they had done this.

00:40:13.700 --> 00:40:16.070
And, in fact, we went and
gave them this briefing.

00:40:16.070 --> 00:40:19.460
And we said to them, we've
concluded your lean enterprise.

00:40:19.460 --> 00:40:22.240
And they said,
whoa, no, we're not.

00:40:22.240 --> 00:40:24.220
We have so much more to do.

00:40:24.220 --> 00:40:26.380
Don't tell us we're
a lean enterprise.

00:40:26.380 --> 00:40:30.560
That's the attitude you
want, wonderful program.

00:40:30.560 --> 00:40:33.380
Here's a completely
different area, electronics,

00:40:33.380 --> 00:40:34.190
Rockwell Collins.

00:40:34.190 --> 00:40:37.880
We're going to come back to
them on Thursday with a case

00:40:37.880 --> 00:40:42.190
study of Rockwell Collins,
but they applied lean thinking

00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:45.100
across their whole company
in the office environment,

00:40:45.100 --> 00:40:48.670
as well as in the factory,
and the great results.

00:40:48.670 --> 00:40:51.970
And we'll see data from them
on their operating performance

00:40:51.970 --> 00:40:52.930
tomorrow.

00:40:52.930 --> 00:40:55.700
Health care, many
examples in health care,

00:40:55.700 --> 00:40:59.680
Susan will give you a lot more
when she talks on Thursday,

00:40:59.680 --> 00:41:00.610
but just hear a few.

